---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Professors | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Professors working internationally, covering academic careers abroad, higher education, and global university opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Professors";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Professors working abroad, teaching and researching internationally, and pursuing careers across universities and academic institutions worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/professor-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/professor-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Professor Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Professors conduct research, teach courses, advise students, and contribute to academic knowledge. International academic careers involve positions at universities worldwide, research collaborations across borders, sabbaticals abroad, and visiting professorships at foreign institutions.
      </p>
      <p>
        International academic opportunities exist through universities actively recruiting international faculty, branch campuses of major universities, research institutions, and the global nature of scholarly work that facilitates academic mobility.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Professors working abroad across universities and academic institutions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Professors</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually university-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Academic pressure and burnout', typical: 'Important to include' },
          { need: 'Dependent coverage', why: 'Family accompaniment', typical: 'If bringing family' },
          { need: 'Research travel coverage', why: 'Fieldwork and conferences', typical: 'Consider for travel' },
          { need: 'Sabbatical coverage', why: 'Research leave abroad', typical: 'If sabbatical planned' },
          { need: 'Retirement/pension', why: 'Long-term career planning', typical: 'Varies by institution' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Academic Appointment Types</h3>
      <p>
        Academic positions range from tenure-track to visiting to contract appointments. Coverage varies significantly by appointment type and institution. Permanent positions typically offer comprehensive benefits while short-term appointments may require personal coverage.
      </p>
      <p>
        Understanding your specific appointment terms and corresponding benefits is essential. Sabbaticals and visiting positions may require special arrangements. Research funding may include coverage provisions.
      </p>

      <h3>Academic Stress</h3>
      <p>
        Academic careers involve significant pressure—publish or perish, grant competition, tenure processes, and work-life balance challenges. Mental health support valuable for managing academic career demands.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Research Universities</h3>
      <p>
        Major research institutions. University benefits comprehensive. Research focus. Research universities offer resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Teaching Universities</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching-focused institutions. University benefits. Instruction emphasis. Teaching institutions offer classroom focus.
      </p>

      <h3>Branch Campuses</h3>
      <p>
        International branches of universities. Parent institution benefits often. Local operations. Branch campuses offer familiarity.
      </p>

      <h3>Research Institutes</h3>
      <p>
        Non-university research centers. Institute benefits vary. Research only. Institutes offer specialization.
      </p>

      <h3>Visiting Positions</h3>
      <p>
        Temporary appointments. Coverage varies widely. Short-term focus. Visiting positions need planning.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Professors"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professors working abroad across universities and academic institutions worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Professor Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Doctoral Degree</h3>
      <p>
        PhD or equivalent. Terminal degree in field. Research training. Doctorate is baseline requirement.
      </p>

      <h3>Publications</h3>
      <p>
        Peer-reviewed papers. Book publications. Research record. Publications demonstrate scholarship.
      </p>

      <h3>Teaching Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Course instruction. Student advising. Curriculum development. Teaching record expected.
      </p>

      <h3>Grants and Funding</h3>
      <p>
        Research funding record. Grant management. External support. Funding demonstrates capability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Academic Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Publication demands. Grant competition. Tenure stress. Mental health support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Screen Time</h3>
      <p>
        Writing and research. Online teaching. Email management. Vision care important.
      </p>

      <h3>Sedentary Work</h3>
      <p>
        Office and lab based. Research sitting. Limited activity. Active lifestyle important.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Conference attendance. Research travel. Collaboration visits. Travel coverage valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Research</h3>
      <p>
        Original investigation. Publication production. Grant writing. Research defines scholarship.
      </p>

      <h3>Teaching</h3>
      <p>
        Course instruction. Student supervision. Curriculum development. Teaching fulfills mission.
      </p>

      <h3>Service</h3>
      <p>
        Committee work. Peer review. Department administration. Service supports institution.
      </p>

      <h3>Mentoring</h3>
      <p>
        Graduate advising. Junior faculty support. Student guidance. Mentoring develops field.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>International Mobility</h3>
      <p>
        Global academic market. International appointments. Research collaboration. Coverage must accommodate mobility.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Assistant to full professor. Endowed chairs. Administration transition. Research leadership. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Job Market</h3>
      <p>
        Competitive globally. Field-dependent demand. Internationalization growing. Market challenging but international.
      </p>

      <h3>Work-Life Balance</h3>
      <p>
        Academia challenging for balance. Tenure pressure intense. Location flexibility post-tenure. Balance achievable but difficult.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a professor considering international appointments. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            University benefits usually comprehensive. Appointment type matters. Family coverage typically included. Verify specific terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about sabbatical coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Home institution coverage may continue. International sabbaticals need verification. Supplemental coverage may help. Plan ahead.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do visiting positions include coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Varies widely. Some include full benefits. Others minimal. Verify before accepting. Personal coverage may be needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is academic burnout a real concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Significant issue in academia. Pressure well-documented. Mental health support valuable. Sustainability essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about conference travel coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Usually covered by university. International conference considerations. Verify travel provisions. Research funds may include.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Competitive market. International opportunities growing. Field-dependent variation. Positive for mobile academics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by understanding your appointment type and corresponding benefits. University positions typically offer comprehensive coverage. Verify family and travel provisions. Plan for sabbaticals and visiting positions separately.
      </p>
      <p>
        Professors advance knowledge and educate future generations worldwide. Your coverage should support global academic careers—addressing research travel, accommodating family needs, and protecting your health across academic positions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Academic Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Professors working abroad across universities and academic institutions worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
